(Import [(1aam ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Principle [Schema is the macro-language source of truth for component data, wire, storage, and upgrade behavior. All Spirit, Signal, Nexus, and SEMA operations are declared in schema files first; generated schema types are the source of every operation data type, and handwritten Rust only implements behavior on those generated nouns.] High High Zero [schema signal nexus sema generated-types])) (c9fv ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Constraint [|Schema migration is a workspace-wide structural prerequisite for every deployed persona triad (not just spirit): a contract or storage-schema change requires the running daemon and its redb to migrate coherently. The deploy-restart-update flow means a daemon meeting an existing redb must find no drift or have a sema-upgrade path; without it, any contract edit after first deploy breaks the next restart.|] High High Zero [schema-migration sema-upgrade redb persona-triad daemon deploy])) (k12x ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [Spirit gets an explicit capability to remove intent entries beyond supersession/negation, plus first-class removal-candidate review: a collect-removal-candidates observation flow that uses record certainty/magnitude to surface low-confidence records and archives or emits reviewed Zero-certainty records before retracting them from the hot store.] High Medium Zero [spirit intent-removal removal-candidate certainty])) (py4h ([(Technology (Software (Data SchemaEvolution)))] Decision [|Upgrade mechanisms are live typed SEMA operations on the Asschema: a protocol or database-format change is a typed operation/message, applied as database work and used as source for derived datatype and upgrade/compatibility code. The same library handles record-level and schema-changing operations. Diff operations have three families: Add, Remove, Modify (Modify subdivides into ContainerEmbed, EnumWrap, Reorder, KeyChange)