aults for common operations, complex forms with full metadata for precise control. Both coexist as distinct wire operation roots; the complex root is canonical and the short root expands to a default of it.] Medium Low Zero [spirit nota operation-ladder])) (44dp ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Short-header / signal-type structure: a 64-bit micro-message header (1 root enum + 7 sub-enums) discriminates any object in the namespace in constant time, emitted by every signal contract macro; byte 0 is the ROOT VERB (most universal beingness — Help/Query/Message), bytes 1-7 are the verb-namespace sub-variants. In schema the header is a positional ordered vector of variants [Variant ...]; data-carrying variants (parenthesized name+data) take the first seven slots (0-6) and unit variants (bare PascalCase) follow, so adding a unit variant is a no-op wire upgrade. Root-level variants are limited, nested ones broad. Sub-enums default to one byte (256 variants) but pack tighter by inner-type semantics — Bool in 1 bit, Option in 2, a 16-variant enum in 4 bits — letting SEMA fit smaller than raw rkyv; freed bits encode deeper variant nesting, and multi-byte sub-enums cover >256 variants without exceeding 64 bits. Integers are typed values, not sub-enum kinds. Three sizing tiers: (1) 64-bit micro header, (2) 64-byte summary message (hand-implemented from natural summary fields, basis for a subscription tier), (3) full unrestricted rkyv message.|] Medium Medium Zero [short-header signal sema rkyv encoding verb-namespace enum-packing])) (8u1o ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Clarification [|Common workspace identifiers (record, forward, send, etc.) are stored as enum-encoded composite names; the wire form is the discriminator, not the string, so the namespace is composable across components and enables multilingual labels.|] Medium Minimum Zero [enum-encoding namespace multilingual encoding])) (edqu ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [Contract schemas should be explicit content-addressable layout schemas for rkyv migration] Medium Minimum Zero [contract-schema rkyv content-address migration])) (fry8 ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Decision [|Schema variant namespaces reserve explicit numeric ranges so the encoded form reflects the logical split before deeper payload parsing. Input and Output are partitions of one wire tag space (e.g. a 1-byte ~240-slot enum split roughly two-thirds: ~120 input then ~120 output slots — illustrative, larger enums get larger spaces): the author declares Input and Output separately at the schema level but rkyv merges them into one tag space, so a single tag byte identifies both the variant and its direction, the basis for input/output dispatch at the message layer.|] Medium Medium Zero [schema rkyv tag-space input-output encoding])) (lf7y ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Clarification [|Assembled schema reserves scalar pass-through type references for built-in scalars (String, U64, Boolean and similar Rust primitive/domain-floor types) so the assembled form writes the scalar directly instead of wrapping it as Plain(String). Those reserved names are unavailable for user-defined data types.|] Medium Minimum Zero [assembled-schema scalar type-reference])) (pdbn ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Principle [The root schema-generated signal object carries the signal-frame protocol behavior for rkyv serialization and process-to-process dispatch, integrating caller/process-origin support when that library is ready.] Medium Minimum Zero [signal-frame rkyv signal dispatch])) (pmg5 ([(Technology (Software (Data Serialization)))] Correction [TraceEvent is a transparent newtype or direct ObjectName trace root when its only payload is the activated object name, yielding a single object shape rather than noisy double-delimited NOTA from a one-field struct.] Medium Minimum Zero [trace-event object-name nota newtype]))])